cal stellar tracks\nsuggests that this is a BSS descendant possibly experiencing its core\nhelium-burning phase. The large applicability of the proposed method to most of\nthe globular clusters in our Galaxy opens the possibility to initiate\nsystematic searches for evolved BSSs, thus giving access to still unexplored\nphases of their evolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Dec 2015 11:07:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-20"}
